[[File:Barcastockmarket.jpg|thumb|Stock Market Front Façade]][[File:Barcastockmarket(0).jpg|thumb|Front of the entire building]] The '''Stock Exchange of Barcelona''' (abbreviation, '''BCN''') is a stock exchange located in [[Barcelona]], and is one of the main exchanges in [[Spain]]. It is located in the [[Eixample]] District, on Passeig de Gràcia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.borsabcn.es/esp/aspx/Portada/Portada.aspx|title=Bolsa de Barcelona|website=www.borsabcn.es|accessdate=20 March 2017}}</ref>
==Operations== The exchange opened in 1989, but was officially founded in 1915, becoming one of the four main [[stock exchanges]] in [[Spain]]. In 2001, there were 715 companies that had equity in the exchange. The market cap on the equities totaled about €515.4 billion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sec.gov/divisions/corpfin/cf-noaction/offshore031103.htm|title=Barcelona Stock Exchange, Bilbao Stock Exchange, Madrid Stock Exchange and Valencia Stock Exchange: No Action, Interpretive and/or Exemptive Letter of March 11, 2003|website=www.sec.gov|accessdate=20 March 2017}}</ref>
