{{Infobox organization | name = Fédération Internationale Féline |image = File:Fédération_Internationale_Féline_logo.jpg |image_border = |size = 150px |alt = |caption = Logo of the FIFe | motto = | formation = 1949 | founders = Marguérite Ravel | abbreviation = FIFe | location_city = | area_served = Worldwide | leader_title = President | leader_name = Annette Sjödin | leader_title2 = Vice President | leader_name2 = Dietmar Sagurski | board_of_directors = Annette Sjödin, Dietmar Sagurski, Eric Reijers, Charles Spijker, Leo van de Haterd, Karl Preiss | key_people = | num_members = | homepage = {{URL|fifeweb.org}} }}
The '''Fédération Internationale Féline''' ('''FIFe''') is a federation of [[cat registry|cat registries]]. There are currently forty-two member organizations in forty countries. Membership spans [[Europe]], [[South America]], and [[Asia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fifeweb.org/wp/org/org_mem.php|title=Fédération Internationale Féline - Members|publisher=fifeweb.org |date= |accessdate=2017-12-28}}</ref> FIFe is one of the nine members of the [[World Cat Congress]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcatcongress.org/wp/org_mem.php|title=The Members of the WCC|publisher=worldcatcongress.org |date= |accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref>
==History== Founded by Marguerite Ravel, the federation was unofficially started in 1949 in [[Paris, France|Paris]], [[France]], at a meeting between the ''Fédération Féline Française'' (French Cat Federation), the Royal Cat Society of Flanders and the [[Associazione Nazionale Felina Italiana|Società Felina Italiana]] (Italian Cat Society). At the organisation's first general assembly, in [[Ghent, Belgium|Ghent]], [[Belgium]], the federation was officially founded. The original name was Fédération Internationale Féline d'Europe or FIFE. In 1972 the Brazilian Cat Club joined, making it necessary to change the Euro-centric name of the federation. The "d'Europe" was dropped, and the abbreviation was changed to FIFe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fifeweb.org/wp/org/org_intro.php|title=Fédération Internationale Féline - Introduction to the FIFe|publisher=fifeweb.org |date= |accessdate=2017-12-28}}</ref>
==Organisation== FIFe is organized into national sub-federations (e.g. Felis Britannica in the [[United Kingdom]]) which handle pedigree registrations, cat shows and awards in each country. FIFe's Executive Board and General Assembly are supported by five commissions: *Judges & Standard Commission *Breeding & Registration Commission *Show Commission *Health & Welfare Commission *Disciplinary Commission
== Recognized breeds == Currently the FIFe recognizes 48 official breeds of cats for championship competitions. All breeds are divided into 4 categories and identified with a three-letter code, according to the Easy Mind System (EMS). The EMS is a system used by FIFe, and all its members, to easily identify cats by alphanumeric codes<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fifeweb.org/wp/breeds/breeds_ems.php|title=Fédération Internationale Féline - Easy Mind System|last=|first=|date=|website=fifeweb.org|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-01-05}}</ref>.
