{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}} {{Infobox Former Subdivision |native_name = Gazaria (Crimea) |common_name = Crimea |subdivision = Colony |nation = Republic of Genoa |year_start = 1266 |year_end = 1475 |date_start = |date_end = |event_start = Transfer of Caffa from Golden Horde |event_end = Conquest by the Ottoman forces |p1 = Golden Horde |flag_p1 = Golden Horde flag 1339.svg |p2 = Empire of Trebizond |flag_p2 = |s1 = Kefe Eyalet |flag_s1 = Ottoman flag alternative 2.svg |image_flag = |flag_type = |image_coat = |image_map = Caffa and Theodoro.PNG |image_map_size = 280px |image_map_caption = |capital = Caffa |coordinates = {{Coord|45|2|N|35|22|E|display=inline,title}} |today = Disputed between [[Ukraine]] and [[Russia]]
<!--- Area and population of a given year ---> |stat_year1 = |stat_area1 = |stat_pop1 = |stat_year2 = |stat_area2 = |stat_pop2 = |footnotes = }}
'''Gazara''' (Gazaria is a Russified version of the name; also Cassaria, Cacsarea, Gazaria, Gasaria) is the name given to the [[Republic of Genoa|Genoese]] colonies in [[Crimea]] and around the [[Black Sea]] from the mid-13th century to the late 15th century.
The word is derived from [[Khazaria]], though the [[Khazars]] had ceased to rule over the area by that time.
==Castles== The colony was officially established with transfer of Caffa by [[Möngke Khan]] to the [[Republic of Genoa]], becoming the regional center of the Black Sea colonies. In 1357, Genoeses acquired the colony of Cembalo (today – [[Balaklava]]), in 1365 Genoese completely overtook the city of Soldaia ([[Sudak]]) from Venetian control.
===Crimea===
* Caffa * Cembalo * Soldaia * Vosporo * Sarsona * Capitanatu Gotia (territory of [[Principality of Theodoro|Theodoro]])
===West Black Sea=== Aside of Crimea, Genoa possessed several castles on the western coast of [[Black Sea]] such as the castle of Maurocastro ([[Bilhorod-Dnistrovsky]]) in the estuary of [[Dniester]], the castle of Ginestra near [[Odessa]], the castle of Licostomo ([[Kiliya, Ukraine|Kiliya]]), the colony of [[Constanca]], the colony of Caladda (upstream of Danube).
===Taman peninsula and Tanais=== * Tana ([[Azov]]) * Matrega ([[Tmutarakan]]) * Copa * Mapa ([[Anapa]]) * Batario ([[Novorossiysk]]) * Casto and Layso ([[Sochi]])
===Georgia===
* Chacari ([[Gagra]]) * Santa Sophia ([[Alakhadzi]]) * Pesonqa ([[Pitsunda]]) * Cavo di Buxo ([[Gudauta]]) * Niocoxia ([[New Athos]]) * Sebastopolis ([[Sukhumi]]) * Lo Bati ([[Batumi]])
{{wide image|Genoese fortress in Sudak.jpg|800px|Panorama of Soldaia Castle near [[Sudak]]|center}}
