{{Infobox politician | name = Olli Immonen | image = Olli Immonen.jpg | office = Member of [[Finnish Parliament]] | term_start = 20 April 2011 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|2|12}} | birth_place = [[Nivala|Nivala, Finland]] | nationality = [[Finns|Finnish]] | party = [[Finns Party]] }}
'''Olli Immonen''' (born February 12, 1986 in [[Nivala]]) is a member of the [[Finnish Parliament]] for the [[Finns Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eduskunta.fi/EN/kansanedustajat/Pages/1122.aspx|title=Olli Immonen|access-date=26 July 2015|publisher=[[Finnish Parliament]]}}</ref> and chairman of the nationalist organization [[Suomen Sisu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://olliimmonen.net/esittely/|title=Esittely - Olli Immonen|last=Immonen|first=Olli|access-date=26 July 2015}}</ref>
Immonen received national attention in July 2015 after writing a controversial anti-[[multicultural]] text on his [[Facebook]] page.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/finnish_mp_calls_for_fight_against_nightmare_of_multiculturalism_no_comment_from_party_leadership/8182155|title=Finnish MP calls for fight against "nightmare of multiculturalism", no comment from party leadership|publisher=Yle News, July 26, 2015}}</ref>
