{{Infobox language |name=Seze |nativename= |pronunciation= |states=[[Ethiopia]] |region= West Oromo region |speakers= 3,000 |date=1995 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Omotic]] |fam3=North |fam4=[[Mao languages|Mao]] |fam5=West |iso3=sze |glotto=seze1235 |glottorefname=Seze }} '''Seze''' (or Sezo) is an [[Afro-Asiatic]] [[Omotic]] language, spoken in the western part of [[Ethiopia]], near the town of Begi and just north of the [[Hozo language|Hozo]]-speaking community.
